<p>What philosophy blogs are active in 2025?<span id="more-55003"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-55005 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bosch-phil-blogs-1024x583.jpg" alt="" width="703" height="400" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bosch-phil-blogs-1024x583.jpg 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bosch-phil-blogs-300x171.jpg 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bosch-phil-blogs-768x437.jpg 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bosch-phil-blogs-1536x874.jpg 1536w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bosch-phil-blogs-2048x1166.jpg 2048w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/bosch-phil-blogs-400x228.jpg 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 703px) 100vw, 703px" /></p>
<p>Below is a list of philosophy blogs and blog-newsletters, mostly limited to ones that have been updated at least once in the past month. I&#8217;m sure I&#8217;ve missed some. And some active blogs may have been on a brief hiatus and so unfairly excluded by the &#8220;one month&#8221; update exclusion. So if you have an active philosophy blog that should be on this list, let me know in the comments, and I&#8217;ll add it to the list.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://aestheticsforbirds.com/">Aesthetics for Birds</a></li>
<li><a href="http://alexanderpruss.blogspot.com/">Alexander Pruss&#8217;s Blog</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.ancientphilosophysociety.org/website">Ancient Philosophy Society</a></li>
<li><a href="https://apda.ghost.io/">The APDA Blog</a></li>
